## Phase 3: Component Architecture

### Step 3.1: Build Core Components

**Component Hierarchy:**
```
Atoms (Basic building blocks)
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Button
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Input
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Icon
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Label
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Badge
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Avatar

Molecules (Simple combinations)
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Input with Label
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Button Group
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Search Field
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Select Dropdown

Organisms (Complex patterns)
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Navigation Bar
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Form Section
  ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Card with Actions
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Data Table
```

### Step 3.2: Component Properties Strategy

**Use Figma's Component Properties:**
- **Variants:** Size (sm, md, lg), State (default, hover, active, disabled)
- **Boolean:** Icon, Label, Badge
- **Text:** Label content, Placeholder
- **Instance Swap:** Icon selection

### Step 3.3: Leverage Slots

**For dynamic components:**
```
Component: Dropdown List
- Use Slots to allow designers to add custom list items
- Specify accepted instances (ListItem components only)
- Maintains design system compliance while adding flexibility
```

### Step 3.4: Connect Variables to Components

**Every component property should reference variables:**
```
Button Background Fill ‚Üí component/button/background/default
Button Text Fill ‚Üí component/button/text/default
Button Corner Radius ‚Üí primitive/radius/md
Button Padding ‚Üí primitive/spacing/md
```

