## Starting with shadcn/ui and Customizing

**What is shadcn/ui?**
shadcn/ui is a collection of beautifully designed, accessible components built with Radix UI and Tailwind CSS. Unlike traditional component libraries, you don't install it as a dependency‚Äîyou copy the source code directly into your project and own it.

**Why Start Here?**
- ‚úÖ Pre-built accessible components (WCAG AA compliant)
- ‚úÖ Full source code control (modify anything)
- ‚úÖ Built on Tailwind (easy to customize)
- ‚úÖ Production-ready patterns
- ‚úÖ Saves weeks of component development

**The Problem:** shadcn/ui looks generic out of the box. Everyone using it has the same visual style.

**The Solution:** Use your Figma design system to customize shadcn/ui to match your brand perfectly.

---

### The Workflow: Figma ‚Üí shadcn/ui Customization

**Process Overview:**
1. Install shadcn/ui with default components
2. Extract your Figma design tokens
3. Map your tokens to Tailwind config
4. Customize shadcn component styles
5. Add brand-specific variations
6. Document your customizations

---

### Step 1: Install shadcn/ui Baseline

**Prerequisites:**
- Next.js, Vite, or any React project
- Tailwind CSS installed

**Installation:**

```bash
# Initialize shadcn/ui
npx shadcn-ui@latest init

# Answer the prompts:
# - TypeScript: Yes
# - Style: Default
# - Base color: Slate (we'll customize this)
# - CSS variables: Yes (IMPORTANT: This enables easy theming)
```

**What this creates:**
```
your-project/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ui/           ‚Üê shadcn components go here
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ lib/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ utils.ts      ‚Üê Utility functions
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ tailwind.config.js ‚Üê Tailwind configuration
```

**Install a few components to start:**
```bash
npx shadcn-ui@latest add button
npx shadcn-ui@latest add input
npx shadcn-ui@latest add card
npx shadcn-ui@latest add badge
```

**Test the default look:**
```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"

export default function Page() {
  return (
    <div className="p-8">
      <Button>Default Button</Button>
      <Button variant="secondary">Secondary</Button>
      <Button variant="outline">Outline</Button>
    </div>
  )
}
```

At this point, your components look like everyone else's shadcn/ui. Let's customize them.

---

### Step 2: Export Design Tokens from Figma

**From your Figma design system:**

1. **Export Variables as DTCG JSON**
   - File ‚Üí Variables ‚Üí Export variables
   - Save as `design-tokens.json`

2. **Your exported file will look like:**
```json
{
  "primitive": {
    "color": {
      "blue": {
        "50": { "$value": "#EFF6FF", "$type": "color" },
        "500": { "$value": "#3B82F6", "$type": "color" },
        "900": { "$value": "#1E3A8A", "$type": "color" }
      },
      "gray": {
        "50": { "$value": "#F9FAFB", "$type": "color" },
        "900": { "$value": "#111827", "$type": "color" }
      }
    }
  },
  "semantic": {
    "action": {
      "primary": { "$value": "{primitive.color.blue.500}" }
    }
  }
}
```

---

### Step 3: Map Tokens to Tailwind Config

**shadcn/ui uses CSS variables for theming.** You need to map your Figma tokens to these CSS variables.

**Understanding shadcn's Token Structure:**

shadcn/ui uses HSL (Hue, Saturation, Lightness) format for easy manipulation:

```css
/* Default shadcn variables */
:root {
  --background: 0 0% 100%;        /* White */
  --foreground: 222.2 84% 4.9%;   /* Almost black */
  --primary: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;   /* Default blue */
  --primary-foreground: 210 40% 98%; /* White text on primary */
  --secondary: 210 40% 96.1%;     /* Light gray */
  --secondary-foreground: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%; /* Dark text */
  --muted: 210 40% 96.1%;
  --muted-foreground: 215.4 16.3% 46.9%;
  --accent: 210 40% 96.1%;
  --accent-foreground: 222.2 47.4% 11.2%;
  --border: 214.3 31.8% 91.4%;
  --input: 214.3 31.8% 91.4%;
  --ring: 222.2 84% 4.9%;         /* Focus ring */
  --radius: 0.5rem;               /* Border radius */
  /* ... more variables */
}
```

**Convert Your Hex Colors to HSL:**

Use a conversion script or online tool:

```javascript
// convert-tokens.js
function hexToHSL(hex) {
  // Remove #
  hex = hex.replace('#', '');
  
  // Convert to RGB
  let r = parseInt(hex.substr(0, 2), 16) / 255;
  let g = parseInt(hex.substr(2, 2), 16) / 255;
  let b = parseInt(hex.substr(4, 2), 16) / 255;
  
  // Find min/max
  let max = Math.max(r, g, b);
  let min = Math.min(r, g, b);
  let h, s, l = (max + min) / 2;
  
  if (max === min) {
    h = s = 0; // achromatic
  } else {
    let d = max - min;
    s = l > 0.5 ? d / (2 - max - min) : d / (max + min);
    
    switch (max) {
      case r: h = (g - b) / d + (g < b ? 6 : 0); break;
      case g: h = (b - r) / d + 2; break;
      case b: h = (r - g) / d + 4; break;
    }
    
    h /= 6;
  }
  
  h = Math.round(h * 360);
  s = Math.round(s * 100);
  l = Math.round(l * 100);
  
  return `${h} ${s}% ${l}%`;
}

// Example: Convert your brand blue
console.log(hexToHSL('#3B82F6')); // Output: "217 91% 60%"
```

**Map Your Figma Tokens to shadcn Variables:**

```css
/* app/globals.css */

@layer base {
  :root {
    /* Your Brand Colors (from Figma) */
    --background: 0 0% 100%;                    /* white - Figma: primitive/color/gray/50 */
    --foreground: 222 47% 11%;                  /* dark text - Figma: primitive/color/gray/900 */
    
    --primary: 217 91% 60%;                     /* YOUR brand blue - Figma: primitive/color/blue/500 */
    --primary-foreground: 0 0% 100%;            /* white text on blue */
    
    --secondary: 214 32% 91%;                   /* light gray - Figma: primitive/color/gray/100 */
    --secondary-foreground: 222 47% 11%;        /* dark text */
    
    --muted: 210 40% 96%;                       /* very light gray - Figma: primitive/color/gray/50 */
    --muted-foreground: 215 16% 47%;            /* medium gray text */
    
    --accent: 217 91% 60%;                      /* same as primary, or different accent */
    --accent-foreground: 0 0% 100%;
    
    --destructive: 0 84% 60%;                   /* red - Figma: primitive/color/red/500 */
    --destructive-foreground: 0 0% 100%;
    
    --success: 142 76% 36%;                     /* green - Figma: primitive/color/green/600 */
    --warning: 38 92% 50%;                      /* orange - Figma: primitive/color/yellow/500 */
    
    --border: 214 32% 91%;                      /* Figma: semantic/border/default */
    --input: 214 32% 91%;                       /* same as border */
    --ring: 217 91% 60%;                        /* focus ring - use primary */
    
    --radius: 0.5rem;                           /* 8px - Figma: primitive/radius/md */
  }

  .dark {
    /* Dark Mode (from your Figma dark mode variables) */
    --background: 222 47% 11%;                  /* dark background */
    --foreground: 210 40% 98%;                  /* light text */
    
    --primary: 217 91% 60%;                     /* primary stays same or slightly lighter */
    --primary-foreground: 222 47% 11%;          /* dark text on primary */
    
    --secondary: 217 33% 17%;                   /* dark gray */
    --secondary-foreground: 210 40% 98%;
    
    /* ... map all your dark mode tokens */
  }
}
```

**Tailwind Config Extension:**

```javascript
// tailwind.config.js
module.exports = {
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: {
        // shadcn uses these automatically
        border: "hsl(var(--border))",
        input: "hsl(var(--input))",
        ring: "hsl(var(--ring))",
        background: "hsl(var(--background))",
        foreground: "hsl(var(--foreground))",
        primary: {
          DEFAULT: "hsl(var(--primary))",
          foreground: "hsl(var(--primary-foreground))",
        },
        secondary: {
          DEFAULT: "hsl(var(--secondary))",
          foreground: "hsl(var(--secondary-foreground))",
        },
        // Add custom colors from your Figma system
        brand: {
          50: '#EFF6FF',   // Your primitive/color/blue/50
          100: '#DBEAFE',
          500: '#3B82F6',  // Your primary
          900: '#1E3A8A',
        }
      },
      borderRadius: {
        lg: "var(--radius)",              // 8px
        md: "calc(var(--radius) - 2px)",  // 6px
        sm: "calc(var(--radius) - 4px)",  // 4px
      },
      // Add your Figma spacing scale
      spacing: {
        'xs': '4px',     // primitive/spacing/xs
        'sm': '8px',     // primitive/spacing/sm
        'md': '16px',    // primitive/spacing/md
        'lg': '24px',    // primitive/spacing/lg
        'xl': '32px',    // primitive/spacing/xl
        '2xl': '48px',
        '3xl': '64px',
      },
      // Add your typography scale
      fontSize: {
        'xs': ['12px', { lineHeight: '1.5' }],
        'sm': ['14px', { lineHeight: '1.5' }],
        'base': ['16px', { lineHeight: '1.5' }],
        'lg': ['18px', { lineHeight: '1.5' }],
        'xl': ['20px', { lineHeight: '1.5' }],
        '2xl': ['24px', { lineHeight: '1.3' }],
        '3xl': ['30px', { lineHeight: '1.2' }],
      }
    }
  }
}
```

---

### Step 4: Customize shadcn Component Styles

**The beauty of shadcn:** You own the source code. You can modify any component.

**Example: Customizing the Button Component**

**Default shadcn button** (`components/ui/button.tsx`):

```tsx
// Before customization
const buttonVariants = cva(
  "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md text-sm font-medium ring-offset-background transition-colors focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90",
        destructive: "bg-destructive text-destructive-foreground hover:bg-destructive/90",
        outline: "border border-input bg-background hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground",
        secondary: "bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary/80",
        ghost: "hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground",
        link: "text-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline",
      },
      size: {
        default: "h-10 px-4 py-2",
        sm: "h-9 rounded-md px-3",
        lg: "h-11 rounded-md px-8",
        icon: "h-10 w-10",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
    },
  }
)
```

**Customize to match your Figma design:**

```tsx
// After customization - matches your Figma button specs
const buttonVariants = cva(
  // Base styles - adjusted to your design
  "inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg text-sm font-semibold transition-all duration-200 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50 active:scale-[0.98]",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        // Adjusted to match your Figma button tokens
        default: "bg-primary text-primary-foreground shadow-sm hover:bg-primary/90 hover:shadow-md",
        destructive: "bg-destructive text-destructive-foreground shadow-sm hover:bg-destructive/90",
        outline: "border-2 border-input bg-background hover:bg-secondary hover:border-primary/50",
        secondary: "bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary/80",
        ghost: "hover:bg-secondary/50 hover:text-accent-foreground",
        link: "text-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline hover:text-primary/80",
      },
      size: {
        // Adjusted to match your Figma spacing tokens
        sm: "h-8 px-3 text-xs",       // 32px height - Figma: component/button/height/sm
        default: "h-10 px-4 py-2",    // 40px height - Figma: component/button/height/md
        lg: "h-12 px-6 text-base",    // 48px height - Figma: component/button/height/lg
        icon: "h-10 w-10",
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
    },
  }
)
```

**Key customizations made:**
- Changed `rounded-md` to `rounded-lg` (matches your 12px radius)
- Changed font weight to `font-semibold` (600 from Figma)
- Added `shadow-sm` for subtle elevation
- Added `hover:shadow-md` for lift effect on hover
- Added `active:scale-[0.98]` for press feedback
- Changed outline border from `border` to `border-2` (stronger)
- Adjusted height and padding to match Figma tokens
- Changed transition timing

---

### Step 5: Add Brand-Specific Variations

**Create Custom Variants Beyond shadcn Defaults**

Based on your Figma design system, you might need additional button variants:

```tsx
const buttonVariants = cva(
  // ... base styles
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: "bg-primary text-primary-foreground ...",
        // ... existing variants
        
        // NEW: Your custom variants from Figma
        brand: "bg-gradient-to-r from-brand-500 to-brand-600 text-white shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl hover:from-brand-600 hover:to-brand-700",
        success: "bg-success text-white hover:bg-success/90",
        warning: "bg-warning text-white hover:bg-warning/90",
        soft: "bg-primary/10 text-primary hover:bg-primary/20",
      },
      size: {
        // ... existing sizes
        xs: "h-6 px-2 text-xs",           // Extra small from Figma
        xl: "h-14 px-8 text-lg",          // Extra large from Figma
      },
      // NEW: Add a shape variant (from your Figma components)
      shape: {
        default: "rounded-lg",
        square: "rounded-md",
        pill: "rounded-full",
      }
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: "default",
      size: "default",
      shape: "default",
    },
  }
)

// Update the component props type
export interface ButtonProps
  extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement>,
    VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> {
  asChild?: boolean
}

// Now you can use:
<Button variant="brand" size="xl" shape="pill">Brand Button</Button>
```

---

### Step 6: Systematically Customize All Components

**Repeat for each shadcn component:**

**Input Component** (`components/ui/input.tsx`):

```tsx
// Customize to match Figma input tokens
const Input = React.forwardRef<HTMLInputElement, InputProps>(
  ({ className, type, ...props }, ref) => {
    return (
      <input
        type={type}
        className={cn(
          // Before: Generic shadcn styles
          // "flex h-10 w-full rounded-md border border-input bg-background px-3 py-2 text-sm ring-offset-background file:border-0 file:bg-transparent file:text-sm file:font-medium placeholder:text-muted-foreground focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 disabled:cursor-not-allowed disabled:opacity-50",
          
          // After: Match your Figma input specs
          "flex h-10 w-full rounded-lg border-2 border-input bg-background px-4 py-2 text-base transition-colors file:border-0 file:bg-transparent file:text-sm file:font-medium placeholder:text-muted-foreground hover:border-primary/50 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:border-primary focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-primary/20 disabled:cursor-not-allowed disabled:opacity-50 disabled:bg-muted",
          className
        )}
        ref={ref}
        {...props}
      />
    )
  }
)
```

**Changes:**
- `rounded-md` ‚Üí `rounded-lg` (12px from Figma)
- `border` ‚Üí `border-2` (2px from Figma)
- `px-3` ‚Üí `px-4` (16px padding from Figma)
- `text-sm` ‚Üí `text-base` (16px from Figma)
- Added `hover:border-primary/50` (hover state from Figma)
- Changed focus ring to `ring-primary/20` (lighter focus ring)
- Added `disabled:bg-muted` (disabled background from Figma)

**Card Component** (`components/ui/card.tsx`):

```tsx
// Customize to match Figma card tokens
const Card = React.forwardRef<HTMLDivElement, React.HTMLAttributes<HTMLDivElement>>(
  ({ className, ...props }, ref) => (
    <div
      ref={ref}
      className={cn(
        // Before: "rounded-lg border bg-card text-card-foreground shadow-sm"
        
        // After: Match Figma card specs
        "rounded-xl border-2 border-border bg-card p-6 text-card-foreground shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  )
)
```

